'''Chief Imam of Ghana''' (''also referred to as'' National Chief Imam ''or'' Grand Mufti of Ghana, "or simply" Chief Imam) is a de facto title for the highest Muslim religious authority in [[Ghana]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/religion/artikel.php?ID=336490 | title=Ahmadiyya Head calls on Chief Imam | work=Daily Guide | date=25 November 2014 | agency=GhanaWeb | accessdate=December 11, 2014 | location=Accra, Ghana}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/580958/1/chief-imam-commends-accra-mayor.html | title=Chief Imam Commends Accra Mayor | work=General News | date=14 November 2014 | agency=Modern Agency | author=Mohammed Saani, Ibrahim | location=Accra, Ghana}}</ref>
==Role== Not necessarily leader of any Islamic sect, holder of the office represents the [[Islam in Ghana|Ghanaian Muslim community]] in national affairs, build bridges between the country's many faiths and "support development programmes that sensitize people to their social responsibilities".<ref name="sonsetfubd">{{cite web | url=http://www.sonsetfund.org/about/biography | title=About Dr. Sheikh Osmanu | publisher=Sonsetfund.org | date=2011 | accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref>
==Succession controversies== There have been calls for [[Government of Ghana]] to give constitutional backing to the ''Chief Imam'''s office; as of January 2016, no major initiative has begun to look into the process.<ref name="irbad">{{cite news | url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2014/December-10th/analyst-fears-finding-chief-imams-successor-could-lead-to-chaos.php | title=Analyst fears finding Chief Imam‚Äôs successor could lead to chaos | work=MyJoy | date=10 December 2014 | agency=Myjoyonline | accessdate=December 11, 2014 | author=Tsatro, Mordy Jerry | location=Accra, Ghana}}</ref><ref name="bankuyeli">{{cite news | url=http://www.spyghana.com/controversy-who-succeeds-nuhu-sharubutu/ | title=Controversy: Who succeeds Nuhu Sharubutu | date=22 January 2014 | agency=Spyghana.com | accessdate=December 11, 2014 | author=Bankuyeli, Abubakar Mahama | location=Accra, Ghana}}</ref> <!-- {{Empty section|date=December 2014}}
