{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
'''Jonah Nabon''' was a [[Rabbinical literature|rabbinical scholar]]; born at [[Jerusalem]] in 1713; died there 1760; son of [[Hanun Nabon]].

He was celebrated for his [[Talmud]]ic and [[kabbalah|kabbalistic]] learning, and was the teacher of [[Chaim Joseph David Azulai]] (the ''Chida''). Nabon wrote several works, of which only two have been published, namely:
*''Nechpah ba-Kesef'' (vol. i, Constantinople, 1748; vol. ii, Jerusalem, 1843), [[responsa]]; and
* ''Get Mekushar'', on [[divorce]], in the form of a commentary on "Get Pashut," a work on the same subject by [[Moses ibn Habib]].

