{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Use British English|date=September 2017}} {{For|the 1941 film|Marco Visconti (film)}} {{Infobox person | name = Marco Visconti | image = Marco Visconti 2011.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Marco Visconti in 2011 | birth_name = Marco Visconti | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1978|06|04}} | birth_place = [[Rome]], [[Italy]] | death_date = | death_place = | residence = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]] | alias = Azrael<ref name="ameth01"/> | occupation = Occultist, Musician | website = {{URL|http://www.marcovisconti.org}} }}
'''Marco Visconti''' (born 4 June 1978) is an Italian [[occult]]ist and musician.<ref name="Discogs">{{cite web|title=XP8: Marco Visconti |url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/149439-XP8|website=Discogs|accessdate=3 September 2017|date=3 September 2017}}</ref> He is known for his work with the musical group [[XP8]]<ref name="www.peek-a-boo-magazine.be">{{cite news |title=C-Lekktor interview Marco Visconti from XP8 |url= http://www.peek-a-boo-magazine.be/en/interviews/xp8/ |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> and [[Faderhead]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/555632-Marco-Visconti|title=Marco Visconti|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2017-10-19}}</ref> Under the name '''Azrael'''<ref name="ameth01">{{cite news |title=Classic Greek pronunciation for "Liber XXV: The Star Ruby", performed by Frater Azrael |url= http://ameth.oto-uk.org/liber-xxv-pronunciation-tips/ |accessdate=5 September 2017 |date=5 September 2017}}</ref> Visconti is an past officer<ref name="treadwells01">{{cite news |title=Treadwells Evening Workshop ‚Äì Marco Visconti |url=https://www.treadwells-london.com/event/the-star-ruby-liber-xxv/ |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> of the [[Thelema|Thelemic]] organisation [[Ordo Templi Orientis]] (O.T.O.) in London,<ref name="brutalresonance.com">{{cite news |title=DJ AZRAEL - JULY 2013 MIXTAPE |url= http://www.brutalresonance.com/feature/dj-azrael-july-2013-mixtape/ |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> and scholar of the occult works of English author [[Aleister Crowley]], the founder of the philosophy and religion of [[Thelema]].<ref name="treadwells-london.com">{{cite news |title=Treadwells Evening Mini-Workshop ‚Äì Marco Visconti |url=http://www.treadwells-london.com/event/meeting-aleister-crowley-magic |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> Italian science-fiction author Francesco Dimitri pays tribute to Visconti‚Äôs underground persona through his signature character Dagon in ''La Ragazza dei miei Sogni,''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bloodmemories.it/galleria/approfondimenti/intervista-francesco-dimitri.html|title=Blood Memories intervista Francesco Dimitri|last=Fool|first=The|website=www.bloodmemories.it|language=it-it|access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref> of which a film adaptation was released in 2017, with Visconti-inspired character played by renowned actor [[Nicolas Vaporidis]].
==Early life== Visconti was born in [[Rome]], [[Italy]].<ref name="tovguide.com">{{cite news |title=Marco Visconti Profile |url=http://www.ovguide.com/marco-visconti-9202a8c04000641f8000000000ea249b |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> He studied Political Science at LUISS Guido Carli, Religious Anthropology at La Sapienza University in Rome, and [[Audio Engineering]] at SAE Institute Milano.<ref name="tevensi.uk">{{cite news |title=Liber XXV: The Star Ruby Workshop |url=https://www.evensi.uk/liber-xxv-the-star-ruby-treadwells-books/168928334 |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref>
==Occult== Visconti has been involved in the [[occult]] since the 1990s.<ref name="treadwells01"/> He was initiated into the Minerval degree of [[Ordo Templi Orientis]] at Khem Lodge in Rome, Italy.<ref name="treadwells02">{{cite news |title=A Thelemic Rite: Liber Reguli |url=https://www.treadwells-london.com/tag/crowley/ |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> During the next few years, he advanced through the ''Man of Earth'' degrees of O.T.O., completing the Triad at AMeTh Lodge in London, UK, where he moved in early 2013<ref name="treadwells-london.com" />, and serving as the Lodge's Treasurer (one of the 3 permanent Officer roles) for several years<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.marcovisconti.org/diary-the-wasteland/|title=The Wasteland {{!}} marcovisconti.org|work=marcovisconti.org|access-date=2018-07-20|language=en-GB}}</ref>. In 2015 he war ordained a [[Deacon]] in the [[Ecclesia Gnostica Catholica]].<ref name="treadwells01"/> However, following months of heated debate about alleged abuse in the Order perpetrated at every level of the organisation<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thelemicunion.com/i-have-been-wronged-sex-power-oto/|title=I Have Been Wronged: Sex and Power in the OTO|date=2018-01-30|work=Thelemic Union|access-date=2018-07-20|language=en-US}}</ref>, Visconti decided to resign from it, telling his version of the story on his own website, in a diary-like blog called ''The Wasteland''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.marcovisconti.org/wasteland/|title=The Wasteland {{!}} marcovisconti.org|last=|first=|date=|work=marcovisconti.org|access-date=2018-07-20|language=en-GB}}</ref>.
Visconti is a [[Freemasonry|Freemason]]<ref name="treadwells05">{{cite news |title=Treadwells: Who We Are |url=https://www.treadwells-london.com/team_member/17659 |accessdate=5 September 2017 |date=5 September 2017}}</ref> belonging to the [[United Grand Lodge of England]] and several successive orders, such as the [[Holy Royal Arch]] and the [[Ancient and Accepted Rite for England and Wales and its Districts and Chapters Overseas]].
In the early 2000s he collaborated with Labirinto Stellare, a small independent press, to translate the works of [[Michael Bertiaux]] and [[Kenneth Grant]] in Italian.
==Music== A member of gothic metal band Morgana‚Äôs Kiss sometime during the late ‚Äô90s, in 2001 Visconti formed [[XP8]], an electronic band drawing inspiration by genres such as [[EBM music|EBM]], [[Synth-pop|synthpop]] and [[UK hard house|hard dance]].<ref name="soundsphere">{{cite news |title=FIVE MINUTES WITH XP8 |url=http://www.soundspheremag.com/features/five-minutes-withxp8/ |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> Other members of the band included Marko Resurreccion and Paul Toohill.<ref name="metropolis-records">{{cite news |title=XP8 began in 2001 as a trio including previous singer Paul Toohill |url=http://www.metropolis-records.com/artist/xp8 |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> In 2006, Visconti joined two other projects, [[Unter Null]] (this partnership will only last few months), and Grendel, as member of the live lineup of each band.<ref name="gothicworld.it">{{cite news |title=Intervista agli XP8 |url=http://www.gothicworld.it/webzine/interviste/musica/796-intervista-agli-xp8 |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> 2007 is the year that saw him playing for [[VNV Nation]] on their "Judgement World Tour".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.reflectionsofdarkness.com/artists-u-z-concertreviews-155/1986-vnv-nation--krefeld-2007|title=VNV Nation Krefeld 2007|last=Vorndran|first=Daniela|date=|work=|access-date=2018-01-30|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en-gb}}</ref> A year later, in 2008, he started working with [[Faderhead]],<ref name="faderhead">{{cite news |title=Intervista agli XP8 |url= http://faderhead.com/blog/its-getting-there/ |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> as well as becoming a staple to the live lineup;<ref name="dnalounge">{{cite news |title=DNA Lounge: Faderhead |url=https://www.dnalounge.com/calendar/2012/03-21.html |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> while in 2009 Visconti ended his collaboration with [[Grendel (band)|Grendel]], to focus only on XP8 and Faderhead.<ref name="intravenousmag.co.uk">{{cite news |title=Interview: Marco Visconti (XP8) |url=http://www.intravenousmag.co.uk/2014/03/interview-marco-visconti-xp8.html |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref>
He continued writing music for the XP8‚Äôs songs as well as working on band‚Äôs synth production and arrangements till the band's split in 2014,<ref name="jamsphere">{{cite news |title=XP8: "Andrenochrome" An Alternative Electro Masterpiece! |url=http://jamsphere.com/reviews/xp8-andrenochrome-an-alternative-electro-masterpiece |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref> when everything came to a grinding halt. Quoting various reasons for this decision, among them the dwindling interest in alternative/industrial dance music, a trend that had a long run for almost two decades but that eventually ran dry. In an interview, Visconti also stated that ''‚Äú[...] no one wants to be the old guy in a room full of kids looking at you like a dinosaur: I remember vividly making fun of those old goths that simply didn‚Äôt want to get the fuck out of MY clubs a decade ago, and the last thing I wanted to become was one of them.‚Äù'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.intravenousmag.co.uk/2015/02/interview-xp8.html|title=Interview: XP8|website=www.intravenousmag.co.uk|access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref> - clearly pointing out the necessity to make space for a younger generation to make things vital and vibrant once again.
After the split of XP8, Visconti continued working as a DJ until April 2015, when he decided to go on hiatus from the music scene after a final set at Sheffield's [[Resistanz|Resistanz Festival]].<ref name="regenmag.com">{{cite news |title=Hard times for XP8 |url=http://regenmag.com/news/hard-times-for-xp8/ |accessdate=3 September 2017 |date=3 September 2017}}</ref>
