{{About|the Uru god|other uses|Tiw (disambiguation)}}

{{unreferenced|date=November 2015}}
'''Tiw''', in [[Uros|Uru]] (a pre-Incan people) mythology is a protector of mines, lakes, and rivers. It is closely related to the [[Aymara people|Aymara]] deity of ''[[Anchanchu]]'', a terrible [[demon]] which haunts caves, rivers, and other isolated places.

